params._data: The encoded payload containing the oracle data.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby disabling any functionality that is only available to the owner.

params._mailbox: The mailbox contract used to dispatch the message.
params.receiver: The address of the message recipient.

returns.messageId: The unique identifier of the dispatched message.

params._ism: The address of the interchain security module.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

handle(uint32,bytes32,bytes).notice: Handles incoming interchain messages by decoding the payload and updating state.

interchainSecurityModule().notice: Reference to the interchain security module.

lastData().notice: Stores the raw data of the last received message.

lastSender().notice: Stores the sender of the last received message.

paymentHook().notice: Address for the post-dispatch payment hook.

receivedData().notice: The most recent oracle data received.

request(address,address,uint32,bytes).notice: Dispatches an interchain message via the provided mailbox.

updates(string).notice: Mapping of oracle data updates by key.
